CC ============================================================================
CC MISC.AGF -- Synapse Optics public-domain catalog for LensHH-LT
CC ============================================================================
CC Built from public sources only. Each entry cites its origin in CC comments.
CC Repo memory:
CC   project_misc_agf_public_only          -- no OpticStudio redistribution
CC   project_zemax_air_relative_vacuum     -- VACUUM index < 1, not = 1
CC   project_zemax_agf_ed_status_trap      -- ED line last field MUST be 0
CC   feedback_no_fabrication_glass_codes   -- cite source, do not invent
CC
CC Catalog version: 1.4  (2026-05-17 — added BACD9 for Ross Optical catalog)
CC Maintainer:      Synapse Optics
CC Target consumer: LensHH-LT (vendor stock-lens import for Edmund Optics,
CC                  Thorlabs, Newport, etc., where vendor .zmx files reference
CC                  materials not present in the standard SCHOTT/OHARA/CDGM/
CC                  HOYA/SUMITA/CORNING_FS/CORNING_B/LIGHTPATH catalogs).
CC
CC Air-index convention: Zemax / OpticStudio uses air at 1 atm, 20 C as the
CC n=1 reference. All indices in this file are *relative to air at STP*. For
CC VACUUM this means n approx 0.99973 (since absolute n_vacuum = 1.0 and
CC n_air > 1.0, the ratio is slightly less than 1).
CC
CC AGF format notes:
CC   NM <name> <formula_code> <MIL> <Nd> <Vd> <ExcludeSubs> <Status> <MeltFreq>
CC   Formula codes: 1=Schott, 2=Sellmeier 1, 3=Herzberger, 4=Sellmeier 2,
CC                  5=Conrady, 6=Sellmeier 3, ...
CC   ED line last field (Status): MUST be 0 to avoid the silent-fallthrough
CC   trap where ZEMAX accepts the entry but disables the dispersion formula
CC   evaluation (see project_zemax_agf_ed_status_trap).
CC ============================================================================
CC
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC VACUUM  (relative to air at 1 atm, 20 C, dry, ~330 ppm CO2)
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC Source: B. Edlen, "The refractive index of air", Metrologia 2, 71-80 (1966).
CC         Evaluated at 20 C, 1 atm dry air; reciprocal taken to give
CC         relative-to-air vacuum index per Zemax/OpticStudio convention.
CC
CC Reference values (computed; verify if precision matters):
CC    @ 486.1 nm (F-line): n approx 0.999726
CC    @ 587.6 nm (d-line): n approx 0.999728   <-- catalog table value
CC    @ 656.3 nm (C-line): n approx 0.999729
CC    @ 1064.0 nm        : n approx 0.999730
CC Vd (computed from F/d/C above) approx 90.7
CC
CC Formula: Schott (type 1), constant approximation n^2 = 0.99945607
CC          (= 0.999728^2).
CC Wavelength dependence of n_vacuum_relative is < 6e-6 across 400-1000 nm,
CC so the constant approximation is adequate for ray tracing in vacuum-
CC immersed sections. If higher precision is needed for a specific design,
CC refit using Edlen 1966 or Ciddor 1996 at the actual operating conditions.
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
NM VACUUM 1 0 0.999728 90.7 0 0 1
GC Vacuum, relative to air at 20C 1atm; Edlen 1966; Synapse Optics fit
ED 0.000000 0.000000 0.000000 0.000000 0 0
CD 9.99456074E-001 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000
TD 0.000000 0.000000 0.000000 0.000000 0.000000 0.000000 2.000000E+001
LD 1.000000E-001 1.000000E+002
CC
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC CAF2  (Calcium Fluoride, single-crystal)
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC Source: I.H. Malitson, "A Redetermination of Some Optical Properties of
CC         Calcium Fluoride," Applied Optics 2, 1103-1107 (1963).
CC         Single-crystal CaF2, room temperature (~20 C).
CC
CC Published Sellmeier (Malitson 1963), wavelength in micrometers:
CC   n^2 - 1 = 0.5675888 * L^2 / (L^2 - 0.050263605^2)
CC           + 0.4710914 * L^2 / (L^2 - 0.1003909^2)
CC           + 3.8484723 * L^2 / (L^2 - 34.649040^2)
CC
CC AGF Sellmeier 1 (formula type 2) stores the L_i denominator constants in
CC squared form (units of um^2):
CC   L1 = 0.050263605^2 = 0.002526427
CC   L2 = 0.1003909^2   = 0.010078335
CC   L3 = 34.649040^2   = 1200.555808
CC
CC Reference values (computed from above coefficients; verify if precision matters):
CC    @ 486.1 nm (F-line): n approx 1.437056
CC    @ 587.6 nm (d-line): n approx 1.433880    <-- catalog table value
CC    @ 656.3 nm (C-line): n approx 1.432422
CC Vd (computed F/d/C) approx 93.6
CC
CC Validity (Malitson 1963): 0.23 - 9.7 um.
CC Density 3.18 g/cm^3; TCE approx 19 ppm/K (0-50 C); dn/dT approx -1.07e-5 /K
CC at room temperature, visible.
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
NM CAF2 2 0 1.43388 93.6 0 0 1
GC Calcium fluoride, single crystal; Malitson 1963
ED 1.900000E+001 2.400000E+001 3.180000E+000 0.000000E+000 0 0
CD 5.6758880E-001 2.5264270E-003 4.7109140E-001 1.0078335E-002 3.8484723E+000 1.2005558E+003
TD -1.070000E-005 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 2.000000E+001
LD 2.300000E-001 9.700000E+000
CC
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC SAPPHIRE  (single-crystal Al2O3, ordinary ray)
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC Source: I.H. Malitson and M.J. Dodge, "Refractive Index and Birefringence
CC         of Synthetic Sapphire," J. Opt. Soc. Am. 62, 1405A (1972).
CC         Single-crystal Al2O3, room temperature, ordinary-ray index n_o.
CC
CC Sapphire is uniaxial (n_o != n_e); the ordinary-ray index is used for
CC stock optics where the c-axis is normal to the optical axis (typical
CC for c-cut and a-cut windows / lenses sold as "isotropic sapphire").
CC
CC Published Sellmeier (Malitson & Dodge 1972), wavelength in micrometers:
CC   n_o^2 - 1 = 1.4313493  * L^2 / (L^2 - 0.0726631^2)
CC             + 0.65054713 * L^2 / (L^2 - 0.1193242^2)
CC             + 5.3414021  * L^2 / (L^2 - 18.028251^2)
CC
CC AGF Sellmeier 1 (formula type 2) stores L_i in squared form (um^2):
CC   L1 = 0.0726631^2  = 0.005279927
CC   L2 = 0.1193242^2  = 0.014238265
CC   L3 = 18.028251^2  = 325.017834
CC
CC Reference values (computed):
CC    @ 486.1 nm (F-line): n_o approx 1.7747
CC    @ 587.6 nm (d-line): n_o approx 1.7682    <-- catalog table value
CC    @ 656.3 nm (C-line): n_o approx 1.7651
CC Vd (computed F/d/C) approx 78
CC
CC Validity (Malitson & Dodge 1972): 0.265 - 5.5 um.
CC Density 3.98 g/cm^3; TCE approx 6.7 ppm/K (parallel c-axis), 5.0 ppm/K
CC (perpendicular c-axis); dn/dT approx +1.3e-5 /K at room temperature visible.
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
NM SAPPHIRE 2 0 1.7682 78.0 0 0 1
GC Sapphire ordinary ray; Malitson and Dodge 1972
ED 6.700000E+000 6.700000E+000 3.980000E+000 0.000000E+000 0 0
CD 1.4313493E+000 5.2799270E-003 6.5054713E-001 1.4238265E-002 5.3414021E+000 3.2501783E+002
TD 1.300000E-005 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 2.000000E+001
LD 2.650000E-001 5.500000E+000
CC
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC AL2O3  (alias for SAPPHIRE, same material)
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC Identical Sellmeier to SAPPHIRE above. Some vendor .zmx files (e.g. Edmund)
CC use "AL2O3" as the GLAS name; this entry resolves those without name remapping.
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
NM AL2O3 2 0 1.7682 78.0 0 0 1
GC Aluminum oxide (sapphire), ordinary ray; alias of SAPPHIRE
ED 6.700000E+000 6.700000E+000 3.980000E+000 0.000000E+000 0 0
CD 1.4313493E+000 5.2799270E-003 6.5054713E-001 1.4238265E-002 5.3414021E+000 3.2501783E+002
TD 1.300000E-005 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 2.000000E+001
LD 2.650000E-001 5.500000E+000
CC
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC PMMA  (Poly(methyl methacrylate), atactic, cast or extruded)
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC Source: N. Sultanova, S. Kasarova, I. Nikolov, "Dispersion Properties of
CC         Optical Polymers," Acta Physica Polonica A 116, 585-587 (2009).
CC         Single-term Sellmeier fit over 0.4368 - 1.052 um at 293 K.
CC         Coefficients from refractiveindex.info Sultanova 2009 PMMA page.
CC
CC Published Sellmeier (Sultanova 2009), wavelength in micrometers:
CC   n^2 - 1 = 1.1819 * L^2 / (L^2 - 0.011313)
CC
CC AGF Sellmeier 1 (formula type 2) stores L_i in squared form (um^2). The
CC Sultanova denominator constant is already in um^2, so it maps directly:
CC   K1 = 1.1819, L1 = 0.011313, K2 = L2 = K3 = L3 = 0
CC
CC Reference values (computed from Sellmeier above):
CC    @ 486.1 nm (F-line): n approx 1.49707
CC    @ 587.6 nm (d-line): n approx 1.49061   <-- catalog table value
CC    @ 656.3 nm (C-line): n approx 1.48782
CC Vd (computed F/d/C) approx 53.0
CC
CC Note: Handbook PMMA values are often nd=1.491 / Vd=57.4. The Sultanova
CC single-term fit reproduces nd well but underpredicts Vd vs handbook (the
CC second resonance term is absorbed into the single L1 constant). Acceptable
CC for stock-lens import; for high-precision design, refit with a 3-term
CC Sellmeier from the original tabulated data.
CC
CC Density 1.19 g/cm^3; TCE approx 70 ppm/K (0-50 C); dn/dT approx -1.05e-4
CC /K at room temperature visible (note: negative and large, typical polymer).
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
NM PMMA 2 0 1.49061 53.0 0 0 1
GC Poly(methyl methacrylate); Sultanova Kasarova Nikolov 2009
ED 7.000000E+001 7.000000E+001 1.190000E+000 0.000000E+000 0 0
CD 1.1819000E+000 1.1313000E-002 0.0000000E+000 0.0000000E+000 0.0000000E+000 0.0000000E+000
TD -1.050000E-004 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 2.000000E+001
LD 4.368000E-001 1.052000E+000
CC
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC ACRYLIC  (alias for PMMA, same material)
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC Identical Sellmeier to PMMA above. "Acrylic" is the trade/vendor name
CC commonly used in Edmund and Thorlabs .zmx GLAS lines.
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
NM ACRYLIC 2 0 1.49061 53.0 0 0 1
GC Acrylic polymer; alias of PMMA (Sultanova 2009)
ED 7.000000E+001 7.000000E+001 1.190000E+000 0.000000E+000 0 0
CD 1.1819000E+000 1.1313000E-002 0.0000000E+000 0.0000000E+000 0.0000000E+000 0.0000000E+000
TD -1.050000E-004 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 2.000000E+001
LD 4.368000E-001 1.052000E+000
CC
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC POLYCARB  (Polycarbonate, bisphenol-A based, optical grade)
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC Source: N. Sultanova, S. Kasarova, I. Nikolov, "Dispersion Properties of
CC         Optical Polymers," Acta Physica Polonica A 116, 585-587 (2009).
CC         Single-term Sellmeier fit over 0.4368 - 1.052 um at 293 K.
CC         Coefficients from refractiveindex.info Sultanova 2009 PC page.
CC
CC Published Sellmeier (Sultanova 2009), wavelength in micrometers:
CC   n^2 - 1 = 1.4182 * L^2 / (L^2 - 0.021304)
CC
CC AGF Sellmeier 1 (formula type 2):
CC   K1 = 1.4182, L1 = 0.021304, K2 = L2 = K3 = L3 = 0
CC
CC Reference values (computed):
CC    @ 486.1 nm (F-line): n approx 1.59959
CC    @ 587.6 nm (d-line): n approx 1.58472   <-- catalog table value
CC    @ 656.3 nm (C-line): n approx 1.57863
CC Vd (computed F/d/C) approx 27.9
CC
CC Note: Handbook PC values are often nd=1.585 / Vd=30. As with PMMA, the
CC single-term fit underpredicts Vd. Acceptable for stock-lens import.
CC
CC Density 1.20 g/cm^3; TCE approx 67 ppm/K; dn/dT approx -1.07e-4 /K.
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
NM POLYCARB 2 0 1.58472 27.9 0 0 1
GC Polycarbonate (bisphenol-A); Sultanova Kasarova Nikolov 2009
ED 6.700000E+001 6.700000E+001 1.200000E+000 0.000000E+000 0 0
CD 1.4182000E+000 2.1304000E-002 0.0000000E+000 0.0000000E+000 0.0000000E+000 0.0000000E+000
TD -1.070000E-004 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 2.000000E+001
LD 4.368000E-001 1.052000E+000
