CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC E48R  (Zeonex E48R, cyclo-olefin polymer; Zeon Corporation)
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC Source: N. Sultanova, S. Kasarova, I. Nikolov, "Dispersion Properties of
CC         Optical Polymers," Acta Physica Polonica A 116, 585-587 (2009).
CC         Single-term Sellmeier fit over 0.4368 - 1.052 um at 293 K.
CC         Coefficients from refractiveindex.info Sultanova 2009 ZeonexE48R.
CC
CC Published Sellmeier (Sultanova 2009), wavelength in micrometers:
CC   n^2 - 1 = 1.2969 * L^2 / (L^2 - 0.011721)
CC
CC AGF Sellmeier 1 (formula type 2):
CC   K1 = 1.2969, L1 = 0.011721, K2 = L2 = K3 = L3 = 0
CC
CC Reference values (computed):
CC    @ 486.1 nm (F-line): n approx 1.53774
CC    @ 587.6 nm (d-line): n approx 1.53050   <-- catalog table value
CC    @ 656.3 nm (C-line): n approx 1.52747
CC Vd (computed F/d/C) approx 51.7
CC
CC Note: Handbook E48R values: nd=1.531 / Vd=56. Single-term fit reproduces
CC nd to 0.0005 and underpredicts Vd; acceptable for stock-lens import.
CC
CC Density 1.01 g/cm^3; TCE approx 60 ppm/K (lowest among common optical
CC polymers); dn/dT approx -9.2e-5 /K. Used in injection-molded precision
CC optics (mobile-camera lens stacks, blu-ray pickups, low-cost imagers).
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
NM E48R 2 0 1.53050 51.7 0 0 1
GC Zeonex E48R cyclo-olefin polymer; Sultanova Kasarova Nikolov 2009
ED 6.000000E+001 6.000000E+001 1.010000E+000 0.000000E+000 0 0
CD 1.2969000E+000 1.1721000E-002 0.0000000E+000 0.0000000E+000 0.0000000E+000 0.0000000E+000
TD -9.200000E-005 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 2.000000E+001
LD 4.368000E-001 1.052000E+000
CC
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC EDMUND_REPLICA_POLYMER_152V52  (synthesized; Edmund hybrid-doublet replica)
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC Source: Synthesized 1-term Sellmeier calibrated to match Edmund's
CC         "___BLANK 1.517 52" model-glass spec found in the GLAS lines of
CC         hybrid asphere doublets 49-656 through 49-665. The replica is the
CC         UV-cured polymer layer deposited on a glass substrate; Edmund does
CC         not publish a vendor name or Sellmeier, so the .zmx ships with a
CC         model-glass (nd/Vd-only) entry. LensHH-LT has no model-glass
CC         support (see project_lhlt_model_glass), so we materialize the
CC         model as a named catalog entry to enable .zmx import.
CC
CC Synthesis method (Schmidt-Penninger style, 1-term Sellmeier):
CC   n^2 - 1 = K1 * L^2 / (L^2 - L1)
CC   Fit K1, L1 to (nd, Vd) at d/F/C lines. Iterated L1 by hand; selected
CC   L1 = 0.01160 um^2 giving K1 = 1.25756 and (nd, Vd) = (1.51700, 51.96).
CC   Target was (1.517, 52). Residuals well within the 3-4 sig-fig precision
CC   of Edmund's BLANK spec.
CC
CC Reference values (computed):
CC    @ 486.1 nm (F-line): n approx 1.52401
CC    @ 587.6 nm (d-line): n approx 1.51700   <-- catalog table value
CC    @ 656.3 nm (C-line): n approx 1.51406
CC Vd (computed F/d/C) approx 51.96
CC
CC IMPORTANT: This entry exists ONLY to enable LensHH-LT import of the 9
CC Edmund hybrid-doublet .zmx files. Do NOT use for design work. The actual
CC polymer dispersion is unknown beyond the (nd, Vd) point; the implied
CC Sellmeier shape is an assumption. For real design with these lenses, use
CC the Edmund prescription tables directly or contact Edmund for the UV
CC adhesive vendor (likely Norland NOA or similar).
CC
CC Density, TCE, dn/dT: unknown; left as zeros. The .zmx files this entry
CC replaces also lack these fields.
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
NM EDMUND_REPLICA_POLYMER_152V52 2 0 1.51700 51.96 0 0 1
GC Synthesized Sellmeier for Edmund 49-656..49-665 hybrid-doublet replica
ED 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0 0
CD 1.2575600E+000 1.1600000E-002 0.0000000E+000 0.0000000E+000 0.0000000E+000 0.0000000E+000
TD 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 2.000000E+001
LD 4.000000E-001 7.000000E-001
CC
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC NOA61  (Norland Optical Adhesive No. 61, UV-cured polymer)
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC Source: refractiveindex.info Norland NOA-61 page (Norland datasheet fit).
CC         Original published as Cauchy: n = A + B/L^2 + C/L^4 with
CC         A = 1.5375, B = 0.00829045, C = -0.000211046  (L in um).
CC         Valid 0.450 - 1.55 um per source.
CC
CC AGF storage: Schott formula (type 1) which is a 6-term n^2 polynomial:
CC   n^2 = A0 + A1*L^2 + A2*L^-2 + A3*L^-4 + A4*L^-6 + A5*L^-8
CC Expanding (A + B/L^2 + C/L^4)^2 gives the equivalent Schott coefficients:
CC   A0 = A^2          = 2.363906     (constant n^2 term)
CC   A1 = 0                            (no L^2 polynomial term in Cauchy)
CC   A2 = 2AB          = 0.025493     (L^-2 coefficient)
CC   A3 = B^2 + 2AC    = -0.000580    (L^-4 coefficient)
CC   A4 = 2BC          = -3.500e-6    (L^-6 coefficient)
CC   A5 = C^2          = 4.454e-8     (L^-8 coefficient)
CC
CC Reference values (computed from Cauchy verbatim and verified by
CC re-evaluating the Schott form above; both yield identical n to 6dp):
CC    @ 486.1 nm (F-line): n approx 1.56881
CC    @ 587.6 nm (d-line): n approx 1.55974   <-- catalog table value
CC    @ 656.3 nm (C-line): n approx 1.55561
CC Vd (computed F/d/C) approx 42.40
CC
CC Note: Norland's published spec sheet gives nd~1.557 and Vd~36-37 (vendor
CC measurement). The refractiveindex.info Cauchy fit reproduces a similar
CC nd (1.560 vs 1.557, 0.3% high) but yields higher Vd (42 vs 37). The
CC discrepancy reflects fitting over a broader band vs the vendor's
CC single-spec point. For stock-lens import where NOA61 is used as a
CC cement layer (~10 um thick), either parameterisation is design-safe.
CC
CC Density ~1.23 g/cm^3 cured; TCE ~220 ppm/K (large, typical polymer).
CC dn/dT data not available; leave thermal coefficients at zero.
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
NM NOA61 1 0 1.55974 42.40 0 0 1
GC Norland Optical Adhesive No.61; refractiveindex.info Cauchy fit
ED 2.200000E+002 2.200000E+002 1.230000E+000 0.000000E+000 0 0
CD 2.3639062E+000 0.0000000E+000 2.5493010E-002 -5.8002400E-004 -3.4996600E-006 4.4540400E-008
TD 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 2.000000E+001
LD 4.500000E-001 1.550000E+000
CC
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC ZEONEX_K26R  (Zeon Corporation cyclo-olefin polymer K26R grade)
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC Source: Zeon Corp ZEONEX brochure (200323391, Aug 2019). The brochure's
CC representative-properties table lists ASTM D542 nd for each grade:
CC   K26R: 1.535      K22R: 1.535      E48R: 1.531
CC   F52R: 1.535      T62R: 1.536      330R: 1.509       480R: 1.525
CC No Sellmeier or Vd is published by Zeon. The COP family (E48R per
CC Sultanova 2009) shows Vd ~52-56 in the visible.
CC
CC Synthesis: 1-term Sellmeier calibrated to match (nd=1.535, Vd=56). The
CC Vd target is the typical COP-family value extrapolated from Sultanova
CC E48R data (Vd_E48R = 51.77). Iterated L1 by hand:
CC   K1 = 1.31380, L1 = 0.01080 um^2
CC giving (nd, Vd) computed = (1.53500, 56.26). Both within engineering
CC tolerance of the Zeon spec.
CC
CC Edmund .zmx files reference this material as "ZEONEX_K22R&K26R_2017"
CC (26 surface uses in BiConvex/Aspheric families). The combined name
CC encodes "either K22R or K26R is acceptable for this design"; per the
CC Zeon brochure, K22R and K26R have identical nd (1.535). The patcher
CC Patch-ZmxModelGlass.ps1 substitutes the combined name with ZEONEX_K26R
CC at .zmx-import time.
CC
CC Density 1.01 g/cm^3; TCE 58 ppm/K (Zeon brochure ASTM E831, -50..100C);
CC heat distortion 143C (1.82 MPa). dn/dT for COP visible region ~-1e-4 /K
CC (similar magnitude to E48R; not in Zeon brochure for K26R specifically).
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
NM ZEONEX_K26R 2 0 1.53500 56.26 0 0 1
GC Zeon Corp Zeonex K26R cyclo-olefin polymer; synthesized from Zeon brochure nd=1.535
ED 5.800000E+001 5.800000E+001 1.010000E+000 0.000000E+000 0 0
CD 1.3138000E+000 1.0800000E-002 0.0000000E+000 0.0000000E+000 0.0000000E+000 0.0000000E+000
TD -1.000000E-004 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 2.000000E+001
LD 4.368000E-001 1.052000E+000
CC
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC WATER  (H2O, distilled, at 19 C)
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC Source: M. Daimon and A. Masumura, "Measurement of the refractive index of
CC         distilled water from the near-infrared region to the ultraviolet
CC         region," Applied Optics 46, 3811-3820 (2007), at 19.0 C.
CC         Coefficients from refractiveindex.info H2O/Daimon-19.0C.
CC
CC Published 4-term Sellmeier (Daimon & Masumura 2007), L in micrometers:
CC   n^2 - 1 = 5.672526103e-1 L^2/(L^2 - 5.085550461e-3)
CC           + 1.736581125e-1 L^2/(L^2 - 1.814938654e-2)
CC           + 2.121531502e-2 L^2/(L^2 - 2.617260739e-2)
CC           + 1.138493213e-1 L^2/(L^2 - 1.073888649e+1)
CC
CC AGF storage: Sellmeier 3 (formula code 6), supports 4 K,L pairs.
CC
CC Reference values (computed):
CC    @ 486.1 nm (F-line): n approx 1.33759
CC    @ 587.6 nm (d-line): n approx 1.33347   <-- catalog table value
CC    @ 656.3 nm (C-line): n approx 1.33161
CC Vd (computed F/d/C) approx 55.78
CC
CC Validity: 0.18 - 1.13 um, distilled water at 19 C.
CC Density 0.998 g/cm^3 at 20 C; dn/dT approx -1e-4 /K at room temperature.
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
NM WATER 6 0 1.33347 55.78 0 0 1
GC Distilled water at 19 C; Daimon and Masumura 2007
ED 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 9.980000E-001 -1.000000E-004 0 0
CD 5.6725261E-001 5.0855505E-003 1.7365811E-001 1.8149387E-002 2.1215315E-002 2.6172607E-002 1.1384932E-001 1.0738886E+001
TD -1.000000E-004 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 1.900000E+001
LD 1.800000E-001 1.130000E+000
CC
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC MGF2  (Magnesium fluoride, single-crystal, ordinary ray)
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC Source: M.J. Dodge, "Refractive properties of magnesium fluoride,"
CC         Applied Optics 23, 1980-1985 (1984).
CC         Single-crystal MgF2, room temperature, ordinary-ray index n_o.
CC         MgF2 is uniaxial; the ordinary index is used for stock windows
CC         and lenses sold with c-axis normal to optical axis (typical).
CC
CC Published Sellmeier (Dodge 1984 o-ray), L in micrometers:
CC   n^2 - 1 = 0.48755108 L^2/(L^2 - 0.04338408^2)
CC           + 0.39875031 L^2/(L^2 - 0.09461442^2)
CC           + 2.3120353  L^2/(L^2 - 23.793604^2)
CC
CC AGF Sellmeier 1 (formula type 2) stores L_i squared (um^2):
CC   L1 = 0.04338408^2 = 0.00188218
CC   L2 = 0.09461442^2 = 0.00895199
CC   L3 = 23.793604^2  = 566.13562
CC
CC Reference values (computed):
CC    @ 486.1 nm (F-line): n_o approx 1.38020
CC    @ 587.6 nm (d-line): n_o approx 1.37774   <-- catalog table value
CC    @ 656.3 nm (C-line): n_o approx 1.37665
CC Vd (computed F/d/C) approx 106.4
CC
CC Validity (Dodge 1984): 0.2 - 7.0 um.
CC Density 3.18 g/cm^3; TCE 13.8 ppm/K (perp c-axis), 8.5 ppm/K (parallel);
CC dn/dT approx +1.0e-5 /K (visible, weak temperature dependence).
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
NM MGF2 2 0 1.37774 106.4 0 0 1
GC Magnesium fluoride ordinary ray; Dodge 1984
ED 1.380000E+001 8.480000E+000 3.180000E+000 0.000000E+000 0 0
CD 4.8755108E-001 1.8821824E-003 3.9875031E-001 8.9519887E-003 2.3120353E+000 5.6613562E+002
TD 1.000000E-005 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 2.000000E+001
LD 2.000000E-001 7.000000E+000
CC
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC INFRASIL  (Heraeus IR-grade fused silica)
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC Source: I.H. Malitson, "Interspecimen comparison of the refractive index
CC         of fused silica," J. Opt. Soc. Am. 55, 1205-1209 (1965).
CC         Standard high-purity fused silica Sellmeier. Heraeus Infrasil is
CC         a low-OH grade fused silica with extended IR transmission to
CC         ~3.5 um (vs ~2.2 um for typical UV-grade fused silica). Its
CC         refractive index is indistinguishable from standard fused silica
CC         within the Malitson formula's validity window (0.21 - 3.71 um).
CC
CC Published Sellmeier (Malitson 1965), L in micrometers:
CC   n^2 - 1 = 0.6961663 L^2/(L^2 - 0.0684043^2)
CC           + 0.4079426 L^2/(L^2 - 0.1162414^2)
CC           + 0.8974794 L^2/(L^2 - 9.896161^2)
CC
CC AGF Sellmeier 1 stores L_i squared (um^2):
CC   L1 = 0.0684043^2 = 0.00467914
CC   L2 = 0.1162414^2 = 0.01351206
CC   L3 = 9.896161^2  = 97.934003
CC
CC Reference values (computed):
CC    @ 486.1 nm (F-line): n approx 1.46313
CC    @ 587.6 nm (d-line): n approx 1.45846   <-- catalog table value
CC    @ 656.3 nm (C-line): n approx 1.45641
CC Vd (computed F/d/C) approx 67.82
CC
CC Note: numerically identical to CORNING_FS.AGF HPFS_7980. Kept here under
CC the INFRASIL alias because Thorlabs vendor .zmx files reference this name.
CC
CC Validity (Malitson 1965): 0.21 - 3.71 um.
CC Density 2.20 g/cm^3; TCE 0.55 ppm/K (room temperature, very low);
CC dn/dT approx +1.25e-5 /K (visible).
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
NM INFRASIL 2 0 1.45846 67.82 0 0 1
GC Heraeus Infrasil IR-grade fused silica; Malitson 1965
ED 5.500000E-001 5.500000E-001 2.200000E+000 0.000000E+000 0 0
CD 6.9616630E-001 4.6791400E-003 4.0794260E-001 1.3512060E-002 8.9747940E-001 9.7934003E+001
TD 1.250000E-005 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 2.000000E+001
LD 2.100000E-001 3.500000E+000
CC
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC ZNSE  (Zinc selenide, CVD)
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC Source: T.F. Connolly et al., "Specifications of Raytheon Co. CVD
CC         zinc selenide" (1979). Coefficients from refractiveindex.info
CC         ZnSe/Connolly page.
CC
CC Published Sellmeier (Connolly 1979), L in micrometers:
CC   n^2 - 1 = 4.45813734 L^2/(L^2 - 0.200859853^2)
CC           + 0.467216334 L^2/(L^2 - 0.391371166^2)
CC           + 2.89566290 L^2/(L^2 - 47.1362108^2)
CC
CC AGF Sellmeier 1 stores L_i squared (um^2):
CC   L1 = 0.200859853^2 = 0.040344878
CC   L2 = 0.391371166^2 = 0.153171765
CC   L3 = 47.1362108^2  = 2221.82594
CC
CC Reference values (computed):
CC    @ 486.1 nm (F-line): n approx 2.7756
CC    @ 587.6 nm (d-line): n approx 2.6243    <-- catalog table value
CC    @ 656.3 nm (C-line): n approx 2.5774
CC Vd (computed F/d/C) approx 8.2 (very high dispersion in visible)
CC
CC Note: ZnSe is most commonly used at IR wavelengths (CO2 laser at 10.6 um,
CC thermal imaging 8-12 um) where its dispersion is much lower than in the
CC visible. The published Vd at visible is essentially a curiosity; for IR
CC design, refer to n at the operating wavelength directly.
CC
CC Validity (Connolly 1979): 0.54 - 18.2 um.
CC Density 5.27 g/cm^3; TCE 7.1 ppm/K (20 C); dn/dT approx +6e-5 /K at IR.
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
NM ZNSE 2 0 2.6243 8.20 0 0 1
GC Zinc selenide CVD; Connolly 1979
ED 7.100000E+000 6.400000E+000 5.270000E+000 -8.500000E-002 0 0
CD 4.4581373E+000 4.0344878E-002 4.6721633E-001 1.5317177E-001 2.8956629E+000 2.2218259E+003
TD -8.500000E-005 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 2.000000E+001
LD 5.400000E-001 1.820000E+001
CC
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC ZNS_IR  (Zinc sulfide, hot-pressed multispectral grade) — alias to ZNSE-
CC         dispersion fallback. See note.
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC Source: Two published Sellmeier-like fits exist for ZnS (Klein 1986
CC         hot-pressed; Debenham 1984 cubic ZnS). Both use a non-Sellmeier-1
CC         form (constant + 1/(L^2-L_i) without the L^2 multiplier) that
CC         doesn't map cleanly into AGF Sellmeier 1 or Sellmeier 3.
CC         Rather than ship a fabricated Sellmeier 1 refit, we provide an
CC         alias to ZNSE: both are wide-band IR materials with similar
CC         visible/NIR opacity and comparable n_d (ZnS ~ 2.36, ZnSe ~ 2.62).
CC         The dispersion is *not* identical; this is a deliberate
CC         design-time fallback so .zmx import does not silently fail with
CC         n=1.0 — see project_lhlt_model_glass. For actual IR design with
CC         ZnS, use the vendor's full n(L) tabulation (Klein 1986).
CC
CC Reference values: ZNS nominal n_d at 587.6 nm approx 2.36 (handbook).
CC We store the ZNSE Sellmeier verbatim but list nd=2.36 / Vd=0 so the
CC catalog table shows the conventional ZnS value. The dispersion behavior
CC of the entry will follow ZnSe, however; flag this in any ZnS-critical
CC design.
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
NM ZNS_IR 2 0 2.3600 0 0 0 1
GC Zinc sulfide IR placeholder; uses ZNSE dispersion; nd from handbook
ED 7.100000E+000 6.500000E+000 4.090000E+000 0.000000E+000 0 0
CD 4.4581373E+000 4.0344878E-002 4.6721633E-001 1.5317177E-001 2.8956629E+000 2.2218259E+003
TD 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 2.000000E+001
LD 5.400000E-001 1.300000E+001
CC
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC SILICON  (Crystalline silicon, room temperature)
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC Source: C.D. Salzberg and J.J. Villa, "Infrared Refractive Indexes of
CC         Silicon Germanium and Modified Selenium Glass," J. Opt. Soc. Am.
CC         47, 244-246 (1957). Sellmeier-1 fit by B.J. Tatian 1984
CC         (refractiveindex.info Si/Salzberg page).
CC
CC Published Sellmeier (Salzberg-Villa 1957 / Tatian recast), L in um:
CC   n^2 - 1 = 10.6684293  L^2/(L^2 - 0.301516485^2)
CC           +  0.0030434748 L^2/(L^2 - 1.13475115^2)
CC           +  1.54133408   L^2/(L^2 - 1104^2)
CC
CC AGF Sellmeier 1 stores L_i squared (um^2):
CC   L1 = 0.301516485^2 = 0.0909124
CC   L2 = 1.13475115^2  = 1.2874604
CC   L3 = 1104^2        = 1218816
CC
CC Reference values:
CC    @ 587.6 nm (d-line): formula extrapolates to n_d approx 3.94, NON-
CC                         PHYSICAL: Si is opaque below ~1.1 um. nd field
CC                         set to 3.42 (representative @ 4 um) with Vd=0.
CC    @ 4.000 um         : n approx 3.4253
CC    @ 10.0 um          : n approx 3.4179
CC
CC Validity (Salzberg-Villa 1957): 1.36 - 11 um.
CC Density 2.329 g/cm^3; TCE 2.6 ppm/K; dn/dT approx +1.5e-4 /K (IR).
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
NM SILICON 2 0 3.42500 0 0 0 1
GC Crystalline silicon; Salzberg-Villa 1957 (Tatian 1984 Sellmeier recast)
ED 0.000000E+000 2.600000E+000 2.329000E+000 0.000000E+000 0 0
CD 1.0668429E+001 9.0912369E-002 3.0434748E-003 1.2874604E+000 1.5413341E+000 1.2188160E+006
TD 1.500000E-004 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 2.000000E+001
LD 1.360000E+000 1.100000E+001
CC
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC GERMANIUM  (Single-crystal germanium, room temperature)
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC Source: N.P. Barnes and M.S. Piltch, "Temperature-dependent Sellmeier
CC         coefficients and nonlinear optics average power limit for
CC         germanium," J. Opt. Soc. Am. 69, 178-180 (1979). The 293 K fit
CC         is commonly cited as the "Icenogle 1976 / Barnes-Piltch 1979"
CC         form available on refractiveindex.info Ge/Icenogle page.
CC
CC Published Sellmeier (Icenogle 1976 / Barnes-Piltch 1979 fit), L in um:
CC   n^2 - 1 = 8.28156 + 6.72880 L^2/(L^2 - 0.44105)
CC                     + 0.21307 L^2/(L^2 - 3870.1)
CC
CC The 8.28156 constant maps to AGF Sellmeier 1 as a K-term with L=0 (then
CC the term reduces to K * L^2 / L^2 = K, i.e. constant):
CC   K1 = 8.28156, L1 = 0  (constant term)
CC   K2 = 6.72880, L2 = 0.44105  (mid-IR resonance)
CC   K3 = 0.21307, L3 = 3870.1   (FIR resonance)
CC
CC Reference values:
CC    @ 587.6 nm (d-line): formula extrapolates to NON-PHYSICAL. Ge is
CC                         opaque below ~2 um. nd field set to 4.00
CC                         (representative @ 10 um) with Vd=0.
CC    @ 4.000 um         : n approx 4.0247
CC    @ 10.0 um          : n approx 4.0043
CC
CC Validity (Icenogle 1976): 2.5 - 12 um.
CC Density 5.323 g/cm^3; TCE 5.7 ppm/K; dn/dT approx +4.0e-4 /K (IR,
CC very large — Ge is thermally sensitive in IR systems).
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
NM GERMANIUM 2 0 4.00400 0 0 0 1
GC Single-crystal germanium; Icenogle 1976 / Barnes-Piltch 1979 fit
ED 0.000000E+000 5.700000E+000 5.323000E+000 0.000000E+000 0 0
CD 8.2815600E+000 0.0000000E+000 6.7288000E+000 4.4105000E-001 2.1307000E-001 3.8701000E+003
TD 4.000000E-004 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 2.000000E+001
LD 2.500000E+000 1.200000E+001
CC
CC ===========================================================================
CC  Molded-glass aliases (CDGM / OHARA names with "_MOLD" or "M" suffix)
CC ===========================================================================
CC Vendor stock-lens .zmx files (LightPath molded aspherics; Edmund molded
CC asphere variants) reference glasses by their molded-form designation: e.g.
CC D-LAK6_MOLD, H-ZLAF52_MOLD. These have the same dispersion as the bulk
CC catalog parent within the precision relevant to layout / paraxial design;
CC the molded versions differ only in achievable form tolerances. We materialize
CC them as aliases of the CDGM / OHARA parent so .zmx import resolves cleanly.
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC D-LAK6_MOLD  (alias of CDGM D-LAK6, molded form)
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
NM D-LAK6_MOLD 2 694531 1.693840 53.128245 0 0 1
GC Alias of CDGM D-LAK6 (molded); same Sellmeier
ED 7.500000E+000 9.500000E+000 3.500000E+000 -8.200000E-003 0 0
CD 4.7772312E-001 2.2696229E-002 1.3362337E+000 6.5960530E-003 1.2254344E+000 9.4202757E+001
TD 1.330000E-006 1.270000E-008 -2.360000E-011 5.620000E-007 7.080000E-010 1.990000E-001 2.000000E+001
LD 3.020000E-001 2.325000E+000
CC
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC D-LAK6M  (LightPath molded D-LAK6 — alias of CDGM D-LAK6)
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC LightPath uses the "M" suffix instead of "_MOLD" for the same molded form.
CC Three Thorlabs Geltech aspheric lenses (37-108, 83-681, 83-990) reference
CC this name; without this alias they fail with glass_unresolved.
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
NM D-LAK6M 2 694531 1.693840 53.128245 0 0 1
GC LightPath molded D-LAK6; alias of CDGM D-LAK6
ED 7.500000E+000 9.500000E+000 3.500000E+000 -8.200000E-003 0 0
CD 4.7772312E-001 2.2696229E-002 1.3362337E+000 6.5960530E-003 1.2254344E+000 9.4202757E+001
TD 1.330000E-006 1.270000E-008 -2.360000E-011 5.620000E-007 7.080000E-010 1.990000E-001 2.000000E+001
LD 3.020000E-001 2.325000E+000
CC
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC D-K59_MOLD  (alias of CDGM D-K59, molded form)
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
NM D-K59_MOLD 2 518635 1.517600 63.499991 0 0 1
GC Alias of CDGM D-K59 (molded); same Sellmeier
ED 6.000000E+000 8.000000E+000 2.410000E+000 -2.500000E-003 0 0
CD 1.1209538E+000 6.5790807E-003 1.5269061E-001 2.3572478E-002 1.0750292E+000 1.0630998E+002
TD 4.680000E-006 1.500000E-008 -2.120000E-011 4.000000E-007 4.940000E-010 2.000000E-001 2.000000E+001
LD 3.020000E-001 2.325000E+000
CC
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC H-LAK54_MOLD  (alias of CDGM H-LAK54, molded form)
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
NM H-LAK54_MOLD 2 734515 1.734000 51.485829 0 0 1
GC Alias of CDGM H-LAK54 (molded); same Sellmeier
ED 5.100000E+000 7.400000E+000 4.010000E+000 -8.600000E-003 0 0
CD 1.2077294E+000 1.7638916E-002 7.3741837E-001 6.6651598E-004 1.3574903E+000 9.6993881E+001
TD 5.910000E-006 1.710000E-008 -2.960000E-011 5.650000E-007 5.050000E-010 1.960000E-001 2.000000E+001
LD 3.020000E-001 2.325000E+000
CC
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC H-ZLAF52_MOLD  (alias of CDGM H-ZLAF52, molded form)
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC Note: parent H-ZLAF52 uses Schott formula (type 1, 6-term polynomial in
CC L^2), not Sellmeier. We mirror that exactly so refractive index agrees.
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
NM H-ZLAF52_MOLD 1 806410 1.806099 40.945389 0 0 1
GC Alias of CDGM H-ZLAF52 (molded); same Schott formula
ED 5.800000E+000 7.200000E+000 4.450000E+000 -5.000000E-003 0 0
CD 3.1694345E+000 -1.2437912E-002 3.2210112E-002 1.8145630E-004 8.9065293E-005 -1.9193315E-006
TD 7.460000E-006 1.780000E-008 -1.510000E-010 7.130000E-007 6.480000E-010 2.520000E-001 2.000000E+001
LD 3.650000E-001 1.014000E+000
CC
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC S-NPH1_MOLD  (alias of OHARA S-NPH1, molded form)
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
NM S-NPH1_MOLD 2 808228 1.808095 22.760817 0 0 1
GC Alias of OHARA S-NPH1 (molded); same Sellmeier
ED 8.300000E+000 0.000000E+000 3.290000E+000 2.610000E-002 0 0
CD 1.7515662E+000 1.3500468E-002 3.6400630E-001 6.6824515E-002 2.4787414E+000 1.7075601E+002
TD -6.700000E-006 1.010000E-008 -3.040000E-011 8.910000E-007 1.320000E-009 3.240000E-001 2.500000E+001
LD 4.046560E-001 2.325420E+000
CC
CC ===========================================================================
CC  Vendor-name aliases (other manufacturer or pre-patch glass names)
CC ===========================================================================
CC
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC E-BAF11  (Hikari E-BAF11, alias of HOYA BAF11 — same nd/Vd glass type)
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC Hikari, HOYA, SCHOTT, and SUMITA all manufacture variants of "BAF11"
CC (barium flint, nd~1.667, Vd~48.3). Hikari uses the "E-BAF11" designation.
CC HOYA BAF11 (Schott formula, type 1) is in our HOYA.AGF; we alias the
CC Hikari name to it. One Thorlabs lens (AC254-060-A doublet) uses this name.
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
NM E-BAF11 1 667483 1.66672 48.30 0 0 1
GC Hikari E-BAF11; alias of HOYA BAF11 (Schott formula)
ED 7.200000E+000 8.700000E+000 3.630000E+000 2.200000E-003 0 0
CD 2.7272955E+000 -1.3470236E-002 1.4809271E-002 1.9615335E-003 -1.9787663E-004 1.0851117E-005
TD 5.787910E-006 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 2.300000E+001
LD 3.650100E-001 1.529600E+000
CC
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC ZEONEX_K22R&K26R_2017  (Edmund pre-patch combined-name alias of ZEONEX_K26R)
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC 18 Edmund AsphericPlastic .zmx files still write the combined-name form
CC "ZEONEX_K22R&K26R_2017" in their GLAS lines. The Patch-ZmxModelGlass.ps1
CC pipeline renames this at import time, but only to a temp copy — the source
CC .zmx is unchanged, so Get-ZmxParsedData (which reads raw .zmx) reports the
CC unpatched name and the SQLite glass_names_json shows the combined form.
CC
CC Aliasing here lets the retrofit resolve those rows via MISC instead of
CC depending on patcher temp-file plumbing. Same coefficients as ZEONEX_K26R.
CC (Per Zeon's brochure, K22R and K26R have identical nd=1.535.)
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
NM ZEONEX_K22R&K26R_2017 2 0 1.53500 56.26 0 0 1
GC Edmund combined-name alias of ZEONEX_K26R (K22R and K26R share nd)
ED 5.800000E+001 5.800000E+001 1.010000E+000 0.000000E+000 0 0
CD 1.3138000E+000 1.0800000E-002 0.0000000E+000 0.0000000E+000 0.0000000E+000 0.0000000E+000
TD -1.000000E-004 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 2.000000E+001
LD 4.368000E-001 1.052000E+000
CC
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC BACD9  (older HOYA designation, renamed to BACD16; same Schott formula)
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CC Ross Optical's 2014 .ZMF catalog uses the older Hoya "BACD9" name for what
CC was later renamed BACD16 (nd=1.62041, Vd=60.35). 4 cemented Ross doublets
CC (L-AOC000/007/037/287) reference it. Coefficients mirror HOYA BACD16 from
CC HOYA.AGF (Schott formula type 1).
CC ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
NM BACD9 1 620603 1.62041 60.35 0 0 1
GC Alias of HOYA BACD16 (older Hoya designation BACD9)
ED 6.000000E+000 7.100000E+000 3.520000E+000 -3.000000E-004 0 0
CD 2.5859898E+000 -1.1940432E-002 1.3995502E-002 4.8974502E-004 -3.9120717E-005 2.2611915E-006
TD 1.986760E-006 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 0.000000E+000 2.300000E+001
LD 3.650100E-001 1.529600E+000
